  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2017-11-15T05:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Pell for Performance Act\n\nThis bill amends the Higher Education Act of 1965 to modify the Federal Pell Grant program. Specifically, if a Pell Grant recipient fails to complete an education program within the maximum timeframe for completion, then the Pell Grants received for such program convert to a Federal Direct Unsubsidized Stafford Loan and are subject to repayment, in accordance with applicable terms and conditions."
